_footnotes            = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| population_total                = 13082\n| population_as_of                = [[2010 United States Census|2010]]\n| population_rank                 = \n| population_density_km2          = 323.96\n<!-- for automatic calculation of any density field, use: auto -->| population_density_sq_mi        = 839.08\n| pop_est_footnotes               = <ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\"/>\n| population_est                  = 12100\n| pop_est_as_of                   = 2018\n| population_demonym              = <!-- demonym, e.g. Liverpudlian for someone from Liverpool -->\n| population_note                 = <!-- time zone(s) -->\n| timezone1                       = [[North American Central Time Zone|CST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = -6\n| timezone1_DST                   = [[North American Central Time Zone|CDT]]\n| utc_offset1_DST                 = -5\n| timezone2                       = \n| utc_offset2                     = \n| timezone2_DST                   = \n| utc_offset2_DST                 = <!-- postal codes, area code -->\n| postal_code_type                = ZIP code\n| postal_code                     = 71055\n| postal2_code_type               = <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n| postal2_code                    = \n| area_code_type                  = Area code(s)\n| area_code                       = [[Area code 420|420]]\n| geocode                         = \n| iso_code                        = \n| registration_plate              = <!-- website, footnotes -->\n| website                         = {{URL|www.mindenusa.com| Minden, Louisiana}}\n| footnotes                       = \n| blank_name                      = [[Federal Information Processing Standards|FIPS code]]\n| blank_info                      = 22-50885\n}}\n\n'''Minden''' is a small city in, and the [[parish seat]] of, [[Webster Parish, Louisiana|Webster Parish]], in the [[US state]] of [[Louisiana]]. It is located twenty-eight miles east of [[Shreveport, Louisiana|Shreveport]]. As of the 2010 census, the city had a total population of 13,082.\n\n== History ==\nMinden was established in 1836 by Charles Veeder. Native sons include [[Gene Austin]] and [[Louis Dunbar]].\n\nThe town's name is derived from the German city of [[Minden]].\n\nDuring the [[American Civil War|Civil War]], a large [[Confederate Army|Confederate]] encampment was located just east of Minden. It housed about 15,000 Confederate soldiers. The town served as a supply depot for the Confederate Army. Close to thirty Confederate soldiers who died in the Battles of Mansfield and Pleasant Hill are buried in the Old Minden Cemetery.\n\nDuring the [[Great Depression]], one of the two Minden banks failed and a fire destroyed a major section of the downtown area (1931).\n\nOn May 1, 1933, a [[tornado]] occurred in the town, destroying 20% of the homes.\n\n==Geography==\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the city has a total area of 31.0 [[square kilometer|km\u00b2]] (12.0 [[square mile|mi\u00b2]]). 30.8&nbsp;km\u00b2 (11.9&nbsp;mi\u00b2) of it is land and 0.2&nbsp;km\u00b2 (0.1&nbsp;mi\u00b2) of it is water. The total area is 75% water.<ref name=\"GR1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/geographies/reference-files/time-series/geo/gazetteer-files.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2011-04-23|date=2011-02-12|title=US Gazetteer files: 2010, 2000, and 1990}}</ref>\n\n==Demographics==\nAs of the [[census]] of 2000, there were 13,027 people, 5,166 households, and 3,430 families residing in the city.<ref name=\"GR2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> The [[population density]] was 423.0/km\u00b2 (1,095.2/mi\u00b2). There were 5,795 housing units at an average density of 188.2/km\u00b2 (487.2/mi\u00b2). The racial makeup of the city was 46.34% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 52.17% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.31% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.27% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.05% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.21% from [[Race (U.S. Census)|other races]], and 0.65% from two or more races. 0.61% of the population were [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race.\n\nThere were 5,166 households out of which 30.5% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 39.6% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 22.8% had a female householder with no husband present, and 33.6% were non-families. 30.9% of all households were made up of individuals and 15.1% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.44 and the average family size was 3.05.\n\nIn the city the population was spread out with 27.0% under the age of 18, 8.6% from 18 to 24, 25.3% from 25 to 44, 21.2% from 45 to 64, and 17.9% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 37 years. For every 100 females there were 84.0 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 77.7 males.\n\nThe median income for a household in the city was $24,175, and the median income for a family was $31,477. Males had a median income of $28,401 versus $19,199 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $14,114. 26.6% of the population and 21.0% of families were below the [[poverty line]]. 39.3% of those under the age of 18 and 20.1% of those 65 and older were living below the poverty line.\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:First Baptist Church of Minden, LA IMG_0827.JPG|<center>First [[Baptist]] Church at 301 Pennsylvania Avenue; founded in 19th century by George Washington Baines, maternal great-grandfather of [[U.S. President]] [[Lyndon B. Johnson]]</center>\nFile:Main Street in Minden, LA IMG_0821.JPG|<center>Main Street in Minden facing west</center>\nFile:Downtown Minden IMG 1666.JPG|<center>Downtown Minden with the signature water tower in the background</center>\nFile:Academy Park in the Historic District of Minden, LA IMG_0579.JPG|<center>Academy Park in the Minden Historic District, site of the former Minden Male Academy.</center>\nFile:McDonald-Monk House, Minden, LA IMG_7314.JPG|<center>The McDonald-Monk House, built in Victorian style in 1904, in the Historic Residential District, was added in 1986 to the [[National Register of Historic Places]].</center>\nFile:Dorcheat Museum in Minden, LA IMG_0912.JPG|<center>[[Dorcheat Historical Association Museum]].</center>\nFile:Revised picture, Minden, LA, bell IMG_0007.JPG|<center>Historic bell used at the former Webster Parish Courthouse building from 1905 to 1951.</center>\nFile:Revised photo of Minden Cemetery, Minden, LA IMG_2349.JPG|<center>Historic [[Minden Cemetery]] has graves dating from the [[American Civil War]].</center>\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Articles Relating to Minden\n| list =\n{{Webster Parish, Louisiana}}\n{{Shreveport, Louisiana}}\n{{Webster Parish, Louisiana, Representatives}}\n{{Louisiana}}\n}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities in Louisiana]]\n[[Category:Minden, Louisiana| ]]\n[[Category:Cities in the Ark-La-Tex]]\n[[Category:Cities in Webster Parish, Louisiana]]\n[[Category:Parish seats in Louisiana]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1836]]\n[[Category:County seats in the Ark-La-Tex]]\n[[Category:1836 establishments in Louisiana]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Minden\n| official_name           = City of Minden\n| native_name             = <!-- if different from the English name -->\n| native_name_lang        = <!-- ISO 639-2 code e.g. \"fr\" for French. If more than one, use {