e show's later seasons, the main cast participated in a series of interactive fan events. A live audience promotional tour known as Schitt's Creek: Up Close & Personal featuring cast members Eugene Levy, Catherine O'Hara, Dan Levy, Annie Murphy, Emily Hampshire, and Noah Reid premiered in September 2018 in Los Angeles. The event included behind-the-scenes stories; a live question and answer session with the cast; and an audience participation trivia game. Following the initial event's success, the tour was expanded to include stops in several additional U.S. and Canadian cities in 2019. Daniel Levy stated that the tour was meant to both promote the show and thank fans for their support.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pollstar.com/article/whats-up-schitts-creek-the-beloved-tv-show-hits-the-road-142736|title=What's Up 'Schitt's Creek': The Beloved TV Show Hits The Road|last=|first=|date=2019-11-18|website=pollstar.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref>\n\nIn November and December 2019, Schitt's Creek's U.S. broadcaster, Pop TV, staged two immersive fan events in Los Angeles and New York City. These events allowed participants to visit the titular town via a series of \"reimagined\" sets featured on the show.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/an-immersive-schitts-creek-is-popping-up-la-new-york-1249431|title='Schitt's Creek' Pop-Up Coming to L.A. and New York Ahead of Final Season|last=Directo-Meston|first=Danielle|date=2019-10-31|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref>\n\nTo promote the series' sixth and final season in January 2020, CBC and Pop TV commissioned \"groundbreaking\" billboards featuring a same-sex kiss between the show's engaged couple, David and Patrick.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/video/schitts-creek-dan-levy-billboard/|title=Dan Levy on His Groundbreaking 'Schitt's Creek' Billboard|last=Moreau|first=Jordan|date=2020-01-22|website=Variety|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref> Series creator Daniel Levy said it felt \"irresponsible\" not to put the characters kissing on a billboard, as it isn't \"something we see every day\" and is \"banned in multiple countries.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1117691/how-dan-levy-s-badass-schitt-s-creek-billboard-created-a-place-for-people-to-celebrate-love|title=How Dan Levy's Schitt's Creek Billboard Created a Place of Love|last=Harnick|first=Chris|date=2020-01-30|website=E! Online|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Canada|Television}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.cbc.ca/schittscreek/}} at [[CBC Television|CBC]]\n* {{Official website|http://poptv.com/schittscreek}} at [[Pop (U.S. TV channel)|Pop TV]]\n* {{IMDb title|3526078}}\n\n{{ACCT Best Comedy Series|state=collapsed}}\n{{CBC Television Shows (current and upcoming)}}\n{{Schitt's Creek}}\n\n[[Category:2010s Canadian LGBT-related television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Canadian sitcoms]]\n[[Category:2020s Canadian sitcoms]]\n[[Category:2010s LGBT-related sitcoms]]\n[[Category:2015 Canadian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Canadian LGBT-related comedy television series]]\n[[Category:CBC Television shows]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Fictional populated places]]\n[[Category:Gemini and Canadian Screen Award for Best Comedy Series winners]]\n[[Category:Television series about families]]\n[[Category:Television series by Anonymous Content]]\n[[Category:Television series by ITV Studios]]\n[[Category:Television series by Lionsgate Television]]\n[[Category:Television series produced in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Works about social class]]\n[[Category:2020 Canadian television series endings]]\n[[Category:Schitt's Creek]]\n[[Category:2020s Canadian LGBT-related television series]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Ontario]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Canadian television series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Schitt's Creek\n| image                    = File:Schitt's_Creek_logo.png\n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = [[Sitcom]]\n| creator                  = {{unbulleted list|[[Eugene Levy]]|[[Dan Levy (Canadian actor)|Dan Levy]]}}\n| writer                   = \n| director                 = \n| starring                 = {{unbulleted list|Eugene Levy|[[Catherine O'Hara]]|Dan Levy|[[Annie Murphy]]|[[Emily Hampshire]]|[[Jennifer Robertson|Jenn Robertson]]|[[Chris Elliott]]|[[Tim Rozon]]|[[Sarah Levy]]|[[Dustin Milligan]]|[[Noah Reid]]|[[Karen Robinson]]|[[John Hemphill (actor)|John Hemphill]]}}\n| composer                 = \n| country                  = Canada\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 6\n| num_episodes             = 80<!--Only use the number of episodes aired -->\n| list_episodes            = List of Schitt's Creek episodes\n| executive_producer       = {{unbulleted list|Eugene Levy|Daniel Levy|Fred Levy|Andrew Barnsley|Ben Feigin|Kevin White|David West Read}}\n| producer                 = {{unbulleted list|[[Colin Brunton]]|Kosta Orfanidis}}\n| location                 = \n| runtime                  = 22\u201348 minutes\n| company                  = Not a Real Company Productions\n| distributor              = [[ITV Studios#ITV Studios Global Entertainment|ITV Studios Global Entertainment]]\n| network                  = [[Pop (American TV channel)|Pop TV]] & [[CBC Television|CBC]]\n| picture_format           = [[1080i]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| audio_format             = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2015|1|13}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|2020|4|07}}\n| website                  = http://www.cbc.ca/schittscreek/\n| website_title            = CBC Television's ''Schitt'$ Creek''\n| camera                   = [[Single-camera setup|Single-camera]]\n}}\n'''''Schitt's Creek''''' (stylized as '''''Schitt{{sup|$}} Creek''''') is a Canadian television [[sitcom]] created by [[Dan Levy (Canadian actor)|Dan]] and [[Eugene Levy]] that aired on [[CBC Television]] from January 13, 2015 to April 7, 2020.<ref name=\":2\">{{cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/arts/eugene-levy-and-catherine-o-hara-are-up-schitt-s-creek-1.2806231 |title=Eugene Levy and Catherine O'Hara are up Schitt's Creek |date=October 21, 2014 |website=[[CBC News]] |accessdate=October 21, 2014}}</ref> It consists of 80 episodes spread over six seasons.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/danjlevy/status/1108745156059123713|title=To Our Dear Fans...pic.twitter.com/FIXjD3gbzA|first=Dan|last=Levy|date=March 21, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":4\" /> Produced by Not a Real Company Productions,<ref name=\"playback\">{{cite magazine |url=http://playbackonline.ca/2014/02/11/sctv-alums-levy-and-ohara-to-star-in-cbc-comedy/ |title=SCTV alums Levy and O'Hara to star in CBC comedy |last=Cummins |first=Julianna |date=February 11, 2014 |magazine=[[Playback (magazine)|Playback]] |accessdate=January 14, 2015}}</ref> the series follows the trials and tribulations of the formerly wealthy Rose family when they are forced to relocate to Schitt's Creek, a small town they once purchased as a joke.<ref name=\"weisblott\" /> Now living in a motel, Johnny (Eugene Levy) and Moira Rose ([[Catherine O'Hara]])\u2014along with their adult children, David (Dan Levy) and Alexis ([[Annie Murphy]])\u2014must adjust to life without money and with each other.<ref name=\"weisblott\" />\n\nThe series was conceived when Dan Levy wondered how the wealthy families frequently depicted on American [[reality television]] would react if they were stripped of all their money.<ref name=\"out-2015\" /> He further developed the series with his father, Eugene, before pitching the series to several networks in Canada and the United States. The series was first sold to CBC Television in Canada and later to [[Pop (American TV channel)|Pop TV]] in the United States, where it debuted on February 11, 2015.<ref name=\":14\" /> \n\nThe series has won various accolades, including two [[ACTRA Award|ACTRA Awards]] and 18 [[Canadian Screen Awards]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/awards-and-festivals/film-awards/room-hyena-road-lead-early-canadian-screen-award-categories/article29204639/|title=Room, Schitt's Creek dominate Canadian Screen Awards|access-date=December 8, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/winners-the-18th-annual-actra-awards-in-toronto-1028928909|title=Winners: The 18th Annual ACTRA Awards in Toronto {{!}} Markets Insider|last=|first=|date=2020-02-22|website=markets.businessinsider.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-02}}</ref> It is the first Canadian comedy series to be nominated for a [[Critics' Choice Television Award]] for Best Comedy Series and the first to win an [[MTV Movie & TV Award]], winning [[MTV Movie Award for Best Comedic Performance|Best Comedic Performance]] for Dan Levy in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|first=Debra |last=Yeo |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/television/2018/12/13/schitts-creek-becomes-first-canadian-comedy-series-nominated-for-a-critics-choice-award.html |title=Schitt's Creek becomes first Canadian comedy series nominated for a Critics' Choice Award |work=The Star |date=December 13, 2018 |accessdate=January 19, 2019}}</ref> It is also the first program from Pop TV to receive [[Primetime Emmy Award]] nominations, including [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Comedy Series|Outstanding Comedy Series]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/schitts-creek-breaks-first-emmy-nominations-pop-tv-1224564|title=Pop TV President Celebrates 'Schitt's Creek' Emmy Breakthrough: \"Holy S***!\"|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=July 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Synopsis ==\nThe wealthy Rose family\u2014[[Video rental shop|video store]] magnate Johnny ([[Eugene Levy]]), his wife and former soap opera actress Moira ([[Catherine O'Hara]]), and their adult children David and Alexis ([[Dan Levy (TV personality)|Dan Levy]] and [[Annie Murphy (actress)|Annie Murphy]])\u2014lose their fortune after being defrauded by their business manager. They are forced to rebuild their lives with their sole remaining asset: a small town named Schitt's Creek, which Johnny had bought for David as a joke birthday gift in 1991.<ref name=weisblott>[http://o.canada.com/entertainment/cbc-schitts-creek/ \"SCTV stars Levy and O\u2019Hara reunite for a forthcoming CBC sitcom called Schitt\u2019s Creek\"]. [[canada.com]], February 10, 2014.</ref> The Roses relocate to Schitt's Creek, moving into two adjacent rooms in a run-down motel. As the family adjusts to their new lives, their well-to-do attitudes come into conflict with the more provincial residents of Schitt's Creek, including mayor Roland Schitt ([[Chris Elliott]]), his wife Jocelyn ([[Jennifer Robertson|Jenn Robertson]]), and the motel's manager Stevie Budd ([[Emily Hampshire]]).<ref name=weisblott />\n\n==Episodes==\n{{main|List of Schitt's Creek episodes}}\n{{:List of Schitt's Creek episodes}}\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Eugene Levy]] as [[Johnny Rose]]\n* [[Catherine O'Hara]] as [[Moira Rose]]\n* [[Dan Levy (Canadian actor)|Daniel Levy]] as [[David Rose (Schitt's Creek)|David Rose]]\n* [[Annie Murphy]] as [[Alexis Rose]]\n* [[Emily Hampshire]] as Stevie Budd, the motel clerk, and later, motel owner\n* [[Jennifer Robertson|Jenn Robertson]] as Jocelyn Schitt, the mayor's wife\n* [[Chris Elliott]] as Roland Schitt, the mayor\n* [[Tim Rozon]] as Mutt Schitt (seasons 1\u20133; guest season 4), Roland and Jocelyn's son and Alexis's former love interest\n* [[Dustin Milligan]] as Ted Mullens, the town's [[Veterinary physician|veterinarian]], and Alexis's boyfriend\n* [[Sarah Levy]] as Twyla Sands, the caf\u00e9's waitress.\n* [[John Hemphill (actor)|John Hemphill]] as Robert \"Bob\" Currie, proprietor of Bob's Garage and a member of the town council\n* [[Karen Robinson]] as Veronica \"Ronnie\" Lee, a member of the town council\n* [[Noah Reid]] as Patrick Brewer (seasons 4\u20136; recurring season 3), David's business partner and fianc\u00e9\n\n===Recurring===\n* [[Rizwan Manji]] as Ray Butani, the only real estate agent in town and a former member of the town council\n* Marilyn Bellfontaine as Gwen Currie, Bob's wife.\n* [[Robin Duke]] as Wendy Kurtz (season 2 & 5), dress shop owner and David's former employer\n* [[Jasmin Geljo]] as Ivan (seasons 2 & 3), a baker who supplies the motel with pastries\n* [[Ennis Esmer]] as Emir Kaplan (season 5), a travel blogger and Stevie's former love interest\n*[[Steve Lund]] as Jake (seasons 2\u20134, 6), Stevie and David's ex who dates them at the same time.\n\n== Development and production ==\n\n=== Conception ===\nDaniel Levy came up with the idea for the show while watching reality television. He told [[Out (magazine)|Out.com]], \"I had been watching some reality TV at the time and was concentrating on what would happen if one of these wealthy families would lose everything. Would the Kardashians still be the Kardashians without their money?\"<ref name=\"out-2015\">{{cite web |last1=Martin |first1=Michael |title=Dan Levy Discusses Schitt's Creek, His Eyebrows & Being a Sex Object |url=https://www.out.com/television/2015/3/09/dan-levy-discusses-schitts-creek-his-eyebrows-being-sex-object |website=Out.com |accessdate=October 15, 2018|date=March 9, 2015 }}</ref> He turned to his father, Eugene Levy, to help develop the show; Eugene Levy came up with series title. Daniel Levy decided to make the location of Schitt's Creek vague, but in August 2018 said that it is in Canada.<ref name=\"mentalfloss-15facts\">{{cite web|url=http://mentalfloss.com/article/526195/15-funny-facts-about-schitts-creek|title=15 Funny Facts About Schitt's Creek|last1=McCarthy|first1=Erin|website=mentalfloss.com|accessdate=October 15, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"buzzfeed-shittscreeklocation\">{{cite web |last1=Mack |first1=David |title=We Finally Know Where \"Schitt's Creek\" Is Set |url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/davidmack/schitts-creek-us-canada-setting-location-dan-levy |website=buzzfeed.com |publisher=Buzzfeed |accessdate=October 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe Levys initially pitched the show to several networks in Canada and the United States. Cable networks [[HBO]] and [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] passed on the series, while broadcast networks [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] (United States) and the [[CBC Television|CBC]] (Canada) expressed interest. The show was first sold to the CBC, but the Levys decided against ABC as its U.S. broadcaster due to the network's alleged history of creative interference. ''Schitt's Creek'' eventually found a U.S. home on Pop TV after striking a deal with network head Brad Schwartz, who had previously hired Daniel on [[MTV (Canada)|MTV Canada]].<ref name=\":14\" />\n\nDuring the early stages of development, various networks suggested the title of the show be changed to make it sound less profane. The Levys resisted these suggestions and argued \"Schitt\" was a legitimate last name. To prove their point, they brought pages copied from a phone book to the CBC showing listings for individuals with the \"Schitt\" surname. The CBC agreed and allowed the Levys to keep the original title.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/television/2015/01/12/how_eugene_levy_convinced_cbc_to_name_his_show_schitts_creek.html|title=How Eugene Levy convinced CBC to name his show 'Schitt's Creek'|last=Wong|first=Tony|date=January 12, 2015|newspaper=Toronto Star|accessdate=January 13, 2015}}</ref> The name has still faced censorship issues during promotional tours in the United States, with many networks shortening the title or providing extra disclaimers before using it on-air.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://slate.com/human-interest/2015/02/schitt-s-creek-sitcom-polite-reviewers-find-themselves-without-a-paddle.html|title=The Winding Circumlocutions of Schitt's Creek Reviews|last=Friedman|first=Nancy|date=February 16, 2015|website=Slate Magazine|language=en|access-date=July 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nDaniel Levy initially envisioned the series ending with season five, but agreed to a sixth season after receiving a two-year renewal following the show's fourth season.<ref name=\":12\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq.com/story/dan-levy-schitts-creek-final-season-interview|title=Dan Levy Cried Over the End of 'Schitt's Creek' (and You Will Too)|last=Meslow|first=Scott|date=November 13, 2019|website=GQ|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=November 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\n[[Catherine O'Hara]] was the series creators' first choice for the role of eccentric family matriarch, Moira Rose. O'Hara had previously worked with Eugene Levy on [[Second City Television|SCTV]], ''[[Best in Show (film)|Best in Show]]'', ''[[A Mighty Wind]]'', ''[[Waiting for Guffman]]'', and ''[[For Your Consideration (film)|For Your Consideration]]''. She initially turned down Levy's offer to star in ''Schitt's Creek'', citing \"laziness\" and an aversion to long-term projects. Levy reached out to another unnamed actress, but continued to court O'Hara for the role. O'Hara eventually agreed to participate in the presentation pilot with no obligation to continue in the role after ''Schitt's Creek'' was ordered to series. After the show was picked up by the CBC, O'Hara agreed to continue in the role.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/jarettwieselman/eugene-levy-and-catherine-ohara-look-back-on-their-40-year-f|title=Eugene Levy And Catherine O'Hara Look Back On Their 40-Year Friendship|last=Wieselman|first=Jarett|website=BuzzFeed|language=en|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref>\n\n[[Annie Murphy]] was offered the role of spoiled socialite Alexis Rose after actress [[Abby Elliott]], who had portrayed the character in the presentation pilot, was unable to continue when the show was picked up to series, due to scheduling conflicts.<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/04/schitts-creek-annie-murphy-interview.html|title=Annie Murphy Can't Help But Bring Her Schitt's Creek Vocal Fry Home With Her|last=Ivie|first=Devon|date=2018-04-11|website=Vulture|language=en-us|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> Murphy first auditioned for the role in Los Angeles, where Daniel Levy said she stood out due to her \"wonderfully natural likability.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mIHWFOGshKE&t=396s|title=\"Schitt's Creek\": Eugene Levy, Catherine O'Hara, Annie Murphy and Daniel Levy with Ophira Eisenberg|last=92nd Y|date=2016-03-15|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> Eugene Levy was unsure of Murphy's casting because she did not possess the blonde hair he had pictured for the role of Alexis. Murphy was subsequently called back for a second audition for a different role, sarcastic motel clerk Stevie Budd. After this audition, Daniel Levy convinced his father that Murphy could dye her hair blonde, and she was officially cast as Alexis Rose.<ref name=\":10\" />\n\n[[Emily Hampshire]] was cast as the deadpan motel clerk, Stevie Budd, after auditioning for the role in Los Angeles. She originally requested to submit a taped audition on account of her nerves and recurring hives breakouts. Hampshire ultimately agreed to audition in person, but states she has no recollection of the experience. According to Daniel Levy, who was present for the process, Hampshire gave a \"great\" audition, then proceeded to lift her shirt over her head to hide and slowly rocked back and forth. Levy later told Hampshire he found her audition \"charming,\" and she was offered the part of Stevie.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.popsugar.com/node/47164875|title=Emily Hampshire on Her Schitt's Creek Audition, Breaking Character, and the Show's Legacy|last=Messina|first=Victoria|date=2020-02-05|website=POPSUGAR Entertainment|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref>\n\n[[Noah Reid]] was offered the role of David's business partner and love interest, Patrick Brewer, in season three. Daniel Levy was socially familiar with Reid and invited him to audition on the suggestion of [[Stacey Farber]].<ref name=\":11\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FPcVdN9aKjg|title=Ep #1 DAN LEVY {{!}} Good For You Podcast with Whitney Cummings|last=Cummings|first=Whitney|date=2019-11-05|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> Reid had never watched the show before he auditioned and was unsure how long the character would be a part of the series.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.myentertainmentworld.ca/2018/03/noah-reid/|title=Nominee Interview Series: Noah Reid|last=Bedard|first=Kelly|date=2018-03-18|website=My Entertainment World|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.secondcity.com/explosively-endearing-things-uncovered-at-schitts-creek-up-close-personal|title=Explosively Endearing Things Uncovered at 'Schitt's Creek: Up Close & Personal'|website=The Second City|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref> Daniel Levy was not present during the audition process and could not chemistry test with Reid before he was cast.<ref name=\":12\" />\n\nOther cast regulars [[Chris Elliott]] and [[Sarah Levy]] were given the roles of Roland Schitt and Twyla Sands, respectively, without auditioning. Elliott says when Eugene Levy offered him the role of the titular town mayor, he thought, \"Why would I say no?\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sKEyd5StanA|title=Chris Elliott Announces a 6th Season of Schitt's Creek|last=King|first=Larry|date=2018-12-14|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> Sarah Levy, the real-life daughter of Eugene Levy and real-life sister of Daniel Levy, was asked to be a part of the show before it was fully developed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tv-eh.com/2020/01/03/sarah-levy-says-goodbye-to-schitts-creek/|title=Sarah Levy says goodbye to Schitt's Creek {{!}} TV, eh?|website=tv-eh.com|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> She says she was glad not to be cast as Alexis, as being out of her real-life family's orbit on the show allowed her to \"do [her] own thing.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.flare.com/celebrity/schitts-creek-sarah-levy-interview/|title=Sarah Levy Interview: On Working With Eugene and Dan on Schitt's Creek|website=flare.com|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref>\n\n=== Production  ===\n''Schitt's Creek'' is produced by Not a Real Company Productions in association with CBC and Pop TV.<ref name=\"playback\" /> Pop TV joined the production team in season two after the series' first season was produced solely in association with CBC.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/voices/in-contention/streaming-us-global-tv-shows-awards-1203309274/|title=For Awards, the Divide Between U.S., Global TV Shows Is Blurred Thanks to Streaming|last=Schneider|first=Michael|date=August 22, 2019|website=Variety|language=en|url-status=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=August 22, 2019}}</ref> [[ITV Studios|ITV Studios Global Entertainment]] also partnered with the CBC and Pop to distribute the show worldwide.<ref name=\":14\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/01/schitts-creek-netflix-pop-success-story.html|title=The Unlikely Rise of Schitt's Creek|last=Adalain|first=Josef|date=January 16, 2019|website=vulture.com|url-status=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=July 6, 2019}}</ref> Eugene Levy, Dan Levy, Fred Levy, Andrew Barnsley, and Ben Feigin have served as [[executive producer]]s throughout the show's entirety.<ref name=\":6\" /><ref name=\":7\" /><ref name=\":8\" /> Other executive producers have included writers Kevin White (seasons two and three) and David West Read (seasons five and six).<ref name=\":6\" /><ref name=\":7\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://press.poptv.com/releases/schittscreekseasonfive|title=Pop Press|website=press.poptv.com|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://press.poptv.com/releases/Schitts_Creek_Season_6_announcement_date|title=Pop Press|website=press.poptv.com|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref> Eugene Levy served as [[showrunner]] alongside co-creator and son, Dan Levy, during the series' first season; Dan Levy took over as sole showrunner beginning in season two.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/01/dan-levy-schitts-creek-profile.html|title=Dan Levy Made Schitt's Creek With His Dad. But It's His Weird Little Baby.|last=Jung|first=E. Alex|date=2019-01-16|website=Vulture|language=en-us|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref>\n\n''Schitt's Creek'' was part of a \"new direction\" in programming taken by both CBC and Pop TV during the 2014-15 television season.<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=http://playbackonline.ca/2014/05/29/cbc-upfront-hellos-goodbyes-and-new-directions-2/|title=CBC upfront: hellos, goodbyes and 'new directions'|last=May 29|first=Katie Bailey|last2=2014|access-date=2019-12-31}}</ref> Premiering alongside 12 new primetime shows on CBC, the series represented one of the network's efforts to produce more \"serialized, scripted\" content, as well as more \"cable-like\" shows.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/mediacentre/press-release/cbc-reveals-lineup-for-2014-15-television-season-featuring-returning-hits-a|title=CBC REVEALS LINEUP FOR 2014-15 TELEVISION SEASON, FEATURING RETURNING HITS AND 12 NEW PRIMETIME TITLES|last=|first=|date=2014-05-29|work=CBC|access-date=|url-status=live|type=Press Release}}</ref><ref name=\":9\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tv-eh.com/2015/01/19/cbc-not-dead-yet/|title=CBC: Not dead yet {{!}} TV, eh?|last=Wild|first=Diane|date=2015-01-19|website=tv-eh.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-31}}</ref> The series was also the first original, scripted program to air on Pop TV after its re-branding in January 2015. Formerly known as [[History of Pop (American TV channel)|TV Guide Network]], Pop TV was re-branded as a channel \"filled with optimism, passion, funny and excitement.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://press.poptv.com/releases/schittscreek|title=Pop Press|website=press.poptv.com|access-date=2019-12-31}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming style and locations ===\n''Schitt's Creek'' is filmed using a [[Single-camera setup|single camera set-up]] with no live audience or [[laugh track]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://playbackonline.ca/2014/04/09/schitts-creek-starts-production-adds-cast/|title=Schitt's Creek starts production, adds cast|date=April 9, 2014|first=Katie|last=Bailey|website=playbackonline.ca|access-date=July 10, 2019}}</ref> The interior scenes for the first two seasons were filmed at [[Pinewood Toronto Studios]] in Toronto,<ref name=\":0\" /> while interior scenes for season 3 were shot at Dufferin Gate Studios in Toronto.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dufferingate.com/|title=Dufferin Gate Studios \u2013 Toronto|website=dufferingate.com|access-date=November 21, 2016}}</ref> Interior scenes were also filmed at Revival Studios in Toronto for an unknown number of seasons.<ref name=\":15\">{{Cite web|url=http://locationmanagers.org/up-schitts-creek/|title=Up Schitt's Creek|date=2020-03-20|website=Location Managers Guild International|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> The remainder of the series is filmed on location in [[Goodwood, Ontario]], the [[Regional Municipality of Durham]] of the [[Greater Toronto Area]], and [[Mono, Ontario]], where the motel scenes are filmed.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orangeville.com/news-story/4596347-hockley-sets-scene-for-cbc-comedy-starring-eugene-levy/ |title=Hockley sets scene for CBC comedy starring Eugene Levy |last=Halliday |first=Chris |date=June 24, 2014 |work=Orangeville Banner |accessdate=February 19, 2015}}</ref> Goodwood was one of 30 towns scouted for the fictional location of Schitt's Creek before production of the series began in 2014.<ref name=\":13\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbc.ca/comedy/103-surprising-facts-easter-eggs-and-trivia-that-every-schitt-s-creek-fan-should-know-1.5471387|title=103 surprising facts, easter eggs and trivia that every Schitt's Creek fan should know|last=|first=|date=2020-03-02|website=CBC Comedy|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-02}}</ref>  \n\nThe series has filmed in several additional locations during its run. The opening shot of the first season features [[Lisa Vanderpump]]\u2019s former [[Beverly Park]] estate as the facade of the Rose family estate. Interior shots of the Rose family estate were filmed on location in a [[Sistine Chapel]]-inspired mansion in Toronto.<ref name=\":13\" /> Main Street [[Stouffville, Ontario]] served as a filming location for an unspecified number of scenes in the series' first two seasons. Scenes involving the fictional retailer, Blouse Barn, in seasons two and three were filmed on location on Main Street in [[Unionville, Ontario]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yorkregion.com/news-story/5659946-schitt-s-creek-fans-get-up-close-with-tv-stars-in-stouffville/|title=Schitt's Creek fans get up close with TV stars in Stouffville|last=Mason|first=Jim|date=June 3, 2015|website=YorkRegion.com|language=en-CA|access-date=July 10, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.narcity.com/life/this-tiny-town-just-outside-of-toronto-is-the-secret-filming-destination-for-your-favourite-tv-shows-and-movies|title=This Tiny Town Just Outside Of Toronto Is The Secret Filming Destination For Your Favourite TV Shows & Movies|website=narcity.com|language=en-CA|access-date=July 10, 2019}}</ref> In the season four episode \"[[List of Schitt's Creek episodes|The Jazzaguy]],\" scenes involving a spa retreat were filmed on location at Monte Carlo Inn in [[Vaughan|Vaughan, Ontario]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/MonteCarloInns/posts/1570016823052544|title=Monte Carlo Inns|website=facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-10}}</ref> Exterior filming also took place at [[Rattlesnake Point (Canada)|Rattlesnake Point]] in [[Milton, Ontario]] for season five's \"[[List of Schitt's Creek episodes|The Hike]].\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insidehalton.com/whatson-story/9268492-spoiler-alert-episode-of-schitt-s-creek-filmed-in-milton/|title=SPOILER ALERT: Episode of Schitt's Creek filmed in Milton|last=Rosella|first=Louie|date=April 4, 2019|website=InsideHalton.com|language=en-CA|access-date=July 10, 2019}}</ref> In season six's \"[[List of Schitt's Creek episodes|Smoke Signals]],\" the series shot on location at Graydon Hall Manor, a wedding venue in Toronto.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-ca/schitts-creek-season-six-recap-episode-1|title=Schitt's Creek Season 6, Episode 1 Recap: The Roses Are Back On Their Bull-Schitt|last=Newman-Bremang|first=Kathleen|website=refinery29.com|language=en-CA|access-date=2020-01-09}}</ref> The series also filmed in [[Bay Adelaide Centre|Bay-Adelaide Centre]] and [[Toronto-Dominion Centre]] for the season six episode \"[[List of Schitt's Creek episodes|The Pitch]].\"<ref name=\":15\" /> Additional filming for several season six episodes took place at a local motel in [[Brantford|Brantford, Ontario]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.brantfordexpositor.ca/news/local-news/fans-watch-schitts-creek-filming-in-city|title=Fans watch Schitt's Creek filming in city|last=Ruby|first=Michelle|date=2019-06-17|website=Brantford Expositor|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-03}}</ref> \n\n=== Music ===\n''Schitt\u2019s Creek'' features several musical performances from its main and supporting characters. The majority of these performances feature the town singing group, the Jazzagals. The Jazzagals' main members are Moira Rose, Jocelyn Schitt, Twyla Sands, Ronnie Lee, and Gwen Currie. Throughout the series, they have covered \u201c[[It's Raining Men]];\u201d \u201c[[Baby I'm Yours (Barbara Lewis song)|Baby, I'm Yours]];\u201d \"Takin\u2019 It Home;\" \"[[Silent Night]];\" and \"[[Islands in the Stream (song)|Islands in the Stream]].\"<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/article/schitts-creek-moira-rose-career.html|title=Everything We Know About Moira Rose's Showbiz Career on Schitt's Creek|last=Bierly|first=Mandi|date=April 10, 2019|website=vulture.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=July 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn season one's \"[[List of Schitt's Creek episodes|Carl's Funeral]],\" Moira sings an a cappella version of \"[[Danny Boy]]\" as a distraction when Johnny's eulogy goes awry. She performs the same song a second time later in the episode.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nIn season four\u2019s \u201c[[List of Schitt's Creek episodes|Asbestos Fest]],\u201d David and Moira perform a duet known as \u201cThe Number.\u201d This medley of holiday songs was regularly performed at the annual Rose Christmas party and included \u201c[[O Come, All Ye Faithful|Oh Come All Ye Faithful]],\u201d \u201c[[Deck the Halls]],\u201d and \u201c[[God Rest You Merry, Gentlemen|God Rest Ye Merry Gentlemen]].\u201d The song was arranged by Moira's portrayer, Catherine O\u2019Hara.<ref>{{Citation|last=Schitt's Creek|title=Schitt's Creek - Behind the Episode: \"Asbestos Fest\"|date=February 8, 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M-s9KhmuI5w&list=PLyIx941Qzz0HSwMGOzzYo7tzBFB9m9FOZ&index=3|access-date=July 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn season four's \u201c[[List of Schitt's Creek episodes|Open Mic]],\u201d Patrick sings an acoustic cover of [[Tina Turner|Tina Turner's]] \u201c[[The Best (song)|The Best]]\u201d as a declaration of love to David. The song was arranged and performed by Patrick's portrayer, Noah Reid.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/schitts-creek-season-4-episode-6-open-mic-dan-levy-tina-turner-the-best-serenade/|title=How Schitt's Creek Created the Most Romantic Scene on TV {{!}} TV Guide|date=February 28, 2018|website=TVGuide.com|language=en|access-date=July 11, 2019}}</ref> After airing on ''Schitt\u2019s Creek'', Reid's version of the song was released on [[Spotify]] and [[iTunes]], where it reached #1 on the Canadian charts. All proceeds from the single were donated to the Ontario charity, LGBT Youth Line.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://canadianbeats.ca/2018/03/03/noah-reid-hits-1-on-itunes-charts-with-his-cover-of-simply-the-best/|title=Noah Reid hits #1 on iTunes charts with his cover of \"Simply The Best\" {{!}} Canadian Beats Media|last=Bickell|first=Dutch|language=en-US|access-date=July 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn season five's \u201c[[List of Schitt's Creek episodes|The Hospies]],\u201d Alexis auditions for a community theatre production by singing \u201c[[A Little Bit Alexis]],\u201d the theme song from her \"critically reviewed, limited reality series\" of the same name. Alexis\u2019 portrayer, Annie Murphy, who wrote and performed the song for the show, says she drew inspiration from the pop songs of [[Paris Hilton]] and [[Lindsay Lohan|Lindsay Lohan]]. Menno Versteeg and Nixon Boyd of the Canadian band, [[Hollerado]], also helped produce the song.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/television/8500491/schitts-creek-annie-murphy-interview-a-little-bit-alexis-song|title='Schitt's Creek': How Annie Murphy Channeled Britney Spears and Paris Hilton for 'A Little Bit Alexis' Banger|website=Billboard|access-date=July 11, 2019}}</ref> \u201cA Little Bit Alexis\u201d was released as a single on Spotify and iTunes, where it reached #28 on the Canadian charts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.itunescharts.net/can/artists/music/annie-murphy/songs/a-little-bit-alexis-from-schitts-creek/|title=iTunesCharts.net: 'A Little Bit Alexis (From Schitt's Creek)' by Annie Murphy (Canadian Songs iTunes Chart)|website=itunescharts.net|access-date=July 11, 2019}}</ref> Partial proceeds from the single were donated to MusiCounts, a Canadian organization providing music resources to schools in need.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/movies-tv/a31984312/schitts-creek-a-little-bit-alexis-true-story/|title=The Definitive History of 'A Little Bit Alexis'|last=Dibdin|first=Emma|date=2020-04-01|website=ELLE|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n\nIn season five's \u201c[[Life Is a Cabaret (Schitt's Creek)|Life Is a Cabaret]]\u201d, several main characters perform \u201c[[Willkommen]]\u201d from the musical ''[[Cabaret (musical)|Cabaret]]''. Stevie also sings a second number, \u201c[[Maybe This Time (song)|Maybe This Time]],\u201d as her ''Cabaret'' character, [[Sally Bowles]], in the same episode.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/04/schitts-creek-recap-season-5-episode-14-life-is-a-cabaret.html|title=Schitt's Creek Season Finale Recap: Curtain Call|last=Fremont|first=Maggie|date=April 10, 2019|website=vulture.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=July 11, 2019}}</ref> Both songs were performed in front of a live audience during filming.<ref>{{Citation|last=Schitt's Creek|title=Schitt's Creek - Behind the Episode: \"Life is a Cabaret\"|date=April 11, 2019|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uQ_LvUjfe38&list=PLyIx941Qzz0GsSdpCY6So-W7pBu_n9mMw&index=5|access-date=July 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn season six's \"[[List of Schitt's Creek episodes|Happy Ending]],\" the series finale, the Jazzagals sing a cappella versions of [[James Morrison (singer)|James Morrison's]] \"Precious Love\" and [[Tina Turner|Tina Turner's]] \"[[The Best (song)|The Best]]\" at David and Patrick's wedding. Noah Reid's Patrick also sings a portion of [[Mariah Carey|Mariah Carey's]] \"[[Always Be My Baby]]\" as part of his wedding vows to David in the same episode.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/04/schitts-creek-series-finale-recap-season-6-episode-14-happy-ending.html|title=Schitt's Creek Series-Finale Recap: Simply the Best|last=Fremont|first=Maggie|date=2020-04-07|website=Vulture|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n==Broadcast==\n\n=== Original broadcast ===\n''Schitt's Creek'' has been co-broadcast in Canada and the United States since 2015. The show initially premiered on the CBC in Canada on Tuesday, January 13, 2015 at 9:00 pm/9:30 pm NT with back-to-back episodes.<ref name=\":2\" /> It made its debut in the United States on Pop TV on Wednesday, February 11, 2015 at 10:00 pm ET/PT.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2014/10/eugene-levy-schitts-creek-series-pop-856574|title=Pop Picks Up Eugene Levy Comedy 'Schitt's Creek' As First Original Scripted Series|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=October 21, 2014|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=January 8, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|last=Jue|first=Teresa|date=November 17, 2014|title=TVGN rebrand Pop announces lineup for 2015, premieres clip from 'Schitt's Creek'|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2014/11/17/tvgn-rebrand-pop-announces-lineup-for-2015-premieres-clip-from-schitts-creek|magazine=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=February 11, 2015}}</ref> Pop moved the series to an 8:00 pm ET/PT time slot with an encore broadcast at 11:00 pm ET/PT for seasons two through four; it returned to its original 10:00 pm ET/PT time slot for season five.<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://press.poptv.com/releases/scseason2premieredate|title=Pop Press|last=|first=|date=October 22, 2015|website=press.poptv.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=August 19, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://press.poptv.com/releases/SchittsCreekS3|title=Pop Press|last=|first=|date=November 14, 2016|website=press.poptv.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=August 19, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://press.poptv.com/releases/schittscreek_letsgetphysical|title=Pop Press|last=|first=|date=November 12, 2017|website=press.poptv.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=August 19, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"tvline-season5-sept\">{{cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2018/09/24/schitts-creek-season-5-premiere-date-pop/|title=Schitt's Creek Season 5 Gets Premiere Date, Larger Episode Order|last1=Ianucci|first1=Rebecca|website=TVline.com|accessdate=October 15, 2018}}</ref> The series maintained staggered premieres throughout its first five seasons, with new episodes debuting in Canada before being broadcast in the United States. This changed in the final season, with new episodes being broadcast simultaneously in Canada and the United States.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/schitts-creek-gets-premiere-date-for-sixth-final-season-on-pop-tv-1202736543/|title='Schitt's Creek' Gets Premiere Date For Sixth & Final Season On Pop TV|last=Bennett|first=Anita|date=September 17, 2019|website=Deadline|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=September 17, 2019}}</ref> The series finale aired on April 7, 2020 at 8:00 pm ET; it was followed by a one-hour behind-the-scenes retrospective documentary titled ''Best Wishes, Warmest Regards: A Schitt's Creek Farewell''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1130556/some-good-news-schitt-s-creek-is-saying-goodbye-with-a-behind-the-scenes-documentary-special|title=Schitt's Creek Will End With Hour-Long Documentary Special|date=2020-03-12|website=E! Online|accessdate=2020-03-12}}</ref> In the United States, the series finale was ''Schitt's Creek's'' highest-rated episode ever and simulcast on [[Logo TV]] and [[Comedy Central]], which had recently become sibling networks to Pop TV through the [[ViacomCBS]] merger.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/schitts-creek-finale-pop-tv-ratings-1234575047/|title=\u2018Schitt\u2019s Creek\u2019 Finale Delivers Highest-Rated Episode Ever|last=Thorne|first=Will|last2=|first2=|date=2020-04-08|website=Variety|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n=== Other broadcasts ===\nAs of 2019, the series also airs on [[4Music]] in the UK; [[Viacom 18]] in India; [[Fox (Asian TV channel)|Fox Asia]]; and [[ABC Comedy]] in Australia.<ref name=\":5\">https://www.tvguide.co.uk/mobile/channellisting.asp?ch=506#425701113</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/pre-sales-for-noughts-and-crosses-lead-scripted-deals-for-itv-studios-at-mipcom-1203369354/|title=Pre-Sales for 'Noughts and Crosses' Lead Scripted Deals for ITV Studios at Mipcom|last=Dams|first=Tim|date=October 14, 2019|website=Variety|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=October 25, 2019}}</ref> It was previously broadcast in New Zealand by [[TV2 (New Zealand)|TV2]] and [[TVNZ]] on Demand, in Australia by [[ABC (Australian TV channel)|ABC]] and its [[ABC iview|iView]] streaming service, and on [[Comedy Central (Indian TV channel)|Comedy Central]] in India.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/shows/schitts-creek|title=Schitt's Creek|website=tvnz.co.nz|access-date=October 25, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/comedycentralin/status/1085763645550874625|title=Schitt's Creek is back better than ever! Catch the Season 5 Premiere tonight only on Comedy Central India. In the US, the show premiered on Comedy Central on April 7, 2020. =@SchittsCreek {{!}} TONIGHT {{!}} 10 PMpic.twitter.com/4XQPRBh923|date=January 16, 2019|website=@comedycentralin|language=en|access-date=October 27, 2019}}</ref> The five seasons appear, though not always together, on different streaming television services worldwide. Netflix carries the full series for viewers in the U.S., UK, Ireland, Japan, South Africa, and Australia. IMDb TV, a streaming service available through [[IMDb]], and CW Seed, a streaming service for the American [[The CW|CW network]], also carry the first five seasons for viewers in the U.S.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/schitts-creek-cw-seed-acquires-off-season-streaming-rights-pop-tv-comedy-tca-1202660736/|title='Schitt's Creek': CW Seed Acquires Off-Season Streaming Rights To Pop TV Comedy \u2013 TCA|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=August 4, 2019|website=Deadline|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=August 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/IMDbTV/status/1241528257230462976|title=PSA: Schitt's Creek seasons 1-5 are free on IMDb TV! No subscription required #IMDbinge https://amzn.to/2WFzGjw\u00a0pic.twitter.com/m1RscZpK7N|last=TV|first=IMDb|date=2020-03-21|website=@IMDbTV|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> \n\nIn December 2019, fans on social media accused UK television station 4Music of censoring some scenes featuring \"intimate dialogue\" and kissing between the show's LGBTQ characters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.out.com/television/2019/12/23/dan-levy-calling-out-network-censoring-schitts-creek|title=Dan Levy Is Calling Out a Network for Censoring 'Schitt's Creek'|last=Street|first=Mikelle|date=2019-12-23|website=out.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-23}}</ref> Co-creator and star, Dan Levy, also addressed the alleged censorship on social media calling it \"highly disturbing\" and \"dangerous.\" 4Music responded to the allegations of censored kissing with an apology, stating that the removal of a kiss between two male characters was \"human error\" and would be restored for future broadcasts. The station did not specifically respond to the allegations of censored dialogue between LGBTQ characters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.advocate.com/television/2019/12/23/dan-levy-calls-out-uk-channel-editing-gay-schitts-creek-scenes|title=Dan Levy Calls Out UK Channel for Editing Gay 'Schitt's Creek' Scenes|last=Linnell|first=Christine|date=2019-12-23|website=advocate.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-23}}</ref>\n\n=== Syndication ===\nIn 2018, [[Debmar-Mercury]], a division of [[Lionsgate]], acquired the U.S. syndication rights to ''Schitt's Creek.'' The series is scheduled to debut in syndication on [[Fox Television Stations]] throughout the U.S. during the Fall 2020 television season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/10/schitts-creek-fox-television-stations-acquired-syndication-deal-h-lionsgates-debmar-mercury-1202750883/|title=Fox Television Stations Acquire Comedy 'Schitt's Creek'|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=October 3, 2019|website=Deadline|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=October 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical response===\nThe first season of ''Schitt's Creek'' received generally positive reviews. It holds an approval rating of 61% on [[Rotten Tomatoes]] based on 23 reviews, with an average rating of 6.38/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"The title is one of the best jokes of ''Schitt's Creek'', but performances from Eugene Levy and Catherine O'Hara give the writing a comedic boost.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/schitts-creek/s01/ |title=Schitt's Creek : Season 1 |website=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=April 19, 2018}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the first season has a score of 64 out of 100, based on 11 critics, indicating \"generally favourable reviews.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/schitts-creek/ |title=Schitt's Creek : Season 1 |website=Metacritic |accessdate=April 19, 2018}}</ref> Vinay Menon of the ''[[Toronto Star]]'' wrote that the show \"is one of the best CBC comedies in years.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/2015/01/19/schitts-creek-is-off-to-a-dazzling-start-menon.html|title=Schitt's Creek is off to a dazzling start: Menon \u2013 Toronto Star|date=January 19, 2015|publisher=|accessdate=March 27, 2018}}</ref> After being picked up by [[Pop (U.S. TV network)|Pop]], the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' described the show as \"very funny, beautifully played, [and] sometimes touching,\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/la-et-st-schitts-canadian-creek-review-eugene-levy-20150211-column.html|title=Canadian 'Creek' overflows with good humor|last=Lloyd|first=Robert|website=latimes.com|access-date=November 28, 2016}}</ref> although Mike Hale of ''[[The New York Times]]'' called ''Schitt's Creek'' \"drab and underwritten.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/11/arts/television/review-in-schitts-creek-a-spoiled-little-rich-family-starts-over.html|title=Review: In 'Schitt's Creek,' a Spoiled Little Rich Family Starts Over|first=Mike|last=Hale|date=February 10, 2015|publisher=|accessdate=March 27, 2018|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n\nSubsequent seasons of ''Schitt's Creek'' have been more positively received, with the show growing in popularity after debuting on [[Netflix]] in January 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/01/dan-levy-schitts-creek-profile.html|title=Dan Levy Made Schitt's Creek With His Dad. But It's His Weird Little Baby.|first=E. Alex|last=Jung|date=January 16, 2019|publisher=|accessdate=January 16, 2019|via=Vulture.com}}</ref> On Rotten Tomatoes, seasons 2, 4, and 5 have approval ratings of 100%, with season 4's consensus reading, \"The comedic real estate value rises for ''Schitt's Creek'' in its fourth year, the series gradually maturing into appointment viewing with a big, beating heart beneath its absurdity.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/schitts_creek/s02|title=Schitt's Creek : Season 2|website=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=January 27, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/schitts_creek/s04 |title=Schitt's Creek : Season 4 |website=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=January 27, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/schitts_creek/s05|title=Schitt's Creek : Season 5|website=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=January 27, 2019}}</ref> Bridget Read of ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' wrote that while the series \"started off with typical fish out of water scenarios,\" it has \"fully come into its own, with a whole cast of ''[[Twin Peaks]]''-meets-[[Christopher Guest|Christopher-Guest]]-universe characters that are as equally endearing.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/schitts-creek-watch-dysfunctional-family-comedy-fun|title=Schitt's Creek Is Like Succession\u2014But Fun|first=Bridget|last=Read|date=September 5, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=January 16, 2019|via=Vogue.com}}</ref> In ''[[New York (magazine)|New York Magazine]]'', Maggie Fremont wrote that \"the show takes a few episodes to get into its groove, but once it does, you\u2019ll never want to leave.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/04/schitts-creek-why-arent-you-watching.html|title=Why Aren't You Watching Schitt's Creek Yet?|first=Maggie|last=Fremont|date=April 9, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=January 16, 2019|via=Vulture.com}}</ref> The series has placed on annual best-of lists published by ''[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/tv/g25439321/best-tv-episodes-2018/|title=The 10 Best Episodes of Television in 2018|first=Justin|last=Kirkland|date=December 10, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=January 16, 2019|via=Esquire.com}}</ref> ''[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.glamour.com/gallery/best-tv-series-2018|title=The Best TV Shows of 2018|first=Christopher|last=Rosa|date=December 23, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=January 16, 2019|via=Glamour.com}}</ref> ''[[The New Yorker]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newyorker.com/culture/2018-in-review/my-not-top-ten-television-list-2018-edition|title=My Not-Top-Ten Television List: The Best TV Shows of 2018|first=Emily|last=Nussbaum|date=December 11, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=January 16, 2019|via=Esquire.com}}</ref> and ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/best-tv-episodes-2018-1203051440/|title=The Top 20 TV Episodes of 2018|first=Daniel|last=D'Addario|date=December 13, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=January 16, 2019|via=Variety.com}}</ref> In 2019, the series was named \"The Best Show on TV Right Now\" by ''[[TV Guide]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/schitts-creek-best-show-on-tv/|title=Schitt's Creek Is the Best Show on TV Right Now|last=Gennis|first=Sadie|date=September 9, 2019|website=TV Guide|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=September 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe series has also been praised for its portrayal of a [[pansexual]] character, played by Dan Levy,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.flare.com/celebrity/dan-levy-on-playing-pansexual-on-schitts-creek/|title=Dan Levy Talks Playing Pansexual on Schitt's Creek \u2013 Flare|date=March 31, 2015|work=Flare|access-date=December 8, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vulture.com/2017/11/pansexual-schitts-creek-character-wont-become-caricature.html|title=Dan Levy Won't Make Pansexual&nbsp;Schitt's Creek&nbsp;Character a 'Caricature'|last=Ferber|first=Taylor|work=Vulture|access-date=December 8, 2017|language=en}}</ref> as well as for how David's sexuality is simply accepted by the other characters with no expressions of [[homophobia]] in the storyline.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/11/dan-levy-explains-why-schitts-creek-has-no-homophobia.html|title=Dan Levy Explains Why Homophobia Will Never Infiltrate Schitt's Creek|last=Ivie|first=Devon|work=Vulture|date=November 18, 2018|access-date=January 16, 2019|language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Awards and nominations===\n{{see also|List of awards and nominations received by Schitt's Creek}}\nIn 2015, ''Schitt's Creek''{{'}}s first season received two [[Directors Guild of Canada]] awards from three nominations. At the [[4th Canadian Screen Awards|2016 ceremony]], season 1 received nine [[Canadian Screen Awards]] from 16 nominations. ''Schitt's Creek''<nowiki/>'s second season received 13 nominations at the 5th [[Canadian Screen Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.academy.ca/category/2017-film-nominees/|title=2017 Film Nominees \u2013 Academy.ca|website=Academy.ca|language=en-US|access-date=February 3, 2017}}</ref> In 2018, the series received nominations from the US-based [[MTV Movie & TV Awards]] and the [[Critics' Choice Television Award]]. In 2019, the series was nominated for 15 [[Canadian Screen Awards]] and four [[Primetime Emmy Award]]s, winning the award for Best Performance by an Actress in a Continuing Leading Comedic Role ([[Catherine O'Hara]]) and Best Comedy Program or Series at the Canadian Screen Awards. The same year, the series won [[Dorian Awards]] for TV Comedy of the Year and Unsung TV Show of the Year from the Society of LGBTQ Entertainment Critics.<ref>[https://galeca.org/dorian-awards/ \"Dorian Awards\". GALECA: The Society of LGBTQ Entertainment Critics: Home of The Dorian Awards.] Retrieved October 11, 2019</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ca.hellomagazine.com/film/02019040150689/anne-with-an-e-schitt-s-creek-win-canadian-screen-awards|title=Anne with an E, Schitt's Creek win big at 2019 Canadian Screen Awards|website=ca.hellomagazine.com|language=English|access-date=April 5, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" />\n\n==Other media==\n\n=== Home media ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Title !! Release !! Format !! Region !! Discs !! Distributor || Ref(s)\n|-\n| <center>''Schitt's Creek: The Complete First Season''</center> || <center>August 11, 2015</center> || <center>DVD</center> || rowspan=\"3\"|<center>[[DVD region code#region 1|Region 1]] <small>'''(CA)'''</small></center>|| <center>2</center> || rowspan=\"3\"|<center>[[Entertainment One Films Canada|eOne Films]]</center> || <center><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.amazon.ca/Schitts-Creek-Season-Annie-Murphy/dp/B00WAJ8MZE| title=Schitt's Creek - Season 1| publisher=Amazon.ca| accessdat