, Call 112 and Wako which was premiered by 1st Oct 2015.\n\n<nowiki>{{Stub}}</nowiki>  <nowiki>{{Entertainment-Stub}}</nowiki>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Uncategorized stub|date=April 2020}}\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Dianah Nabatanzi|timestamp=20200415155201|year=2020|month=April|day=15|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Dianah Nabatanzi|date=15 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n'''Nabatanzi Dianah''' is a Ugandan Actress, commercial model, radio and TV personality.\n\n== Education ==\nShe pursued a bachelor\u2019s degree from Ndejje university.\n\n== Work Experience ==\nShe worked with Uganda broadcasting Corporation (UBC)/star TV as a presenter for two years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://chano8.com/a-look-at-rising-actress-nabatanzi-dianah/|title=A Look At Rising Actress 'Nabatanzi Dianah'|last=walter|date=2015-08-20|website=Chano8|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n\nAnd also worked with Pearl FM radio as a presenter for two years. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.howwebiz.ug/news/celebrity/7898/meet-21-yr-old-nabatanzi-dianah-with-a-blossoming-acting-career|title=Meet 21-yr-old Nabatanzi Dianah with A Blossoming Acting Career|last=https://plus.google.com/+HowweBizUg|website=www.howwebiz.ug|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n\nShe worked as a presenter on BBS TV (Terefayina)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCrkQ4OlgtOQICQ4NFTExttw|title=BBS TEREFAYINA|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> and also worked as an active actor in the Ugandan Movie Industry.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://celebcloud.net/tv-presenters/diana-nabatanzi|title=Dianah Nabatanzi {{!}} Actress Profile, Photos, Videos|date=2019-01-24|website=Celeb Cloud|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n\n== Movies she featured in ==\nBwebatyo (Decision of Agony), Sikola, House Arrest, Call 112 and Wako which was premiered by 1st Oct 2015.\n\n\n<nowiki>{{Stub}}</nowiki>  <nowiki>{{Entertainment-Stub}}</nowiki>\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up, addedorphan,uncategorised,deadendtags,typo(s) fixed: bachelor\u2019s degree \u2192 bachelor's degree", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dianah_Nabatanzi"}
{"title_page": "Cariuma", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Cariuma\n| logo = Cariuma logo.png\n| logo_size = 150px\n| founders = David Python<br>Fernando Porto\n| foundation = 2016\n| industry = Clothing\n| website = {{url|https://cariuma.com/}}\n}}\n'''Cariuma''' is a company that produces and sells shoes.\n\n==History==\nCariuma is a designer and manufacturer of sustainably produced [[Sneakers|sneaker-style shoes]], which it retails through the Internet. It was cofounded in 2016<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://danamic.org/2018/12/29/from-rio-to-singapore-cariuma-sneakers-are-now-exclusively-available-at-kapok-ndc/|title=From Rio To Singapore: CARIUMA Sneakers Are Now Exclusively Available at kapok NDC|date=December 29, 2018|website=DANAMIC}}</ref> by David Python<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/directtoconsumer-sneaker-brand-scores-us13m-seed-funding|title=Tech in Asia - Connecting Asia's startup ecosystem|website=www.techinasia.com}}</ref> and Fernando Porto.<ref name=Today>{{Cite web|url=https://www.today.com/shop/popular-cariuma-ibi-sneakers-are-back-stock-t175607|title=Why over 6,000 people are on the waitlist for these sustainably-made sneakers|website=TODAY.com}}</ref> The manufacturing is based in [[Brazil]]<ref name=Maglin>{{Cite web|url=https://www.travelandleisure.com/style/shopping/cariuma-catiba-low-sneakers|title=These Comfy Sneakers Were Handmade for Walking \u2014 and They\u2019re Completely Sustainable|website=Travel + Leisure}}</ref> and [[China]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fastcompany.com/90418251/these-shoes-are-made-from-bamboo-sugar-cane-and-cork-and-totally-carbon-neutral|title=These shoes are made from bamboo, sugarcane, and cork\u2014and are totally carbon neutral|first=Adele|last=Peters|date=October 21, 2019|website=Fast Company}}</ref> while the has offices in [[Singapore]], [[New York City]], [[Los Angeles]], and [[Rio de Janeiro]].<ref name=Parisi>{{Cite web|url=https://www.glossy.co/fashion/1-year-in-how-sneaker-brand-cariuma-is-making-a-1-million-investment-in-sustainability-pay-off|title=1 year in: How sneaker brand Cariuma is making a $1 million investment in sustainability pay off|date=December 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\nCariuma makes its shoes by hand, and uses materials including canvas, leather, and suede,<ref name=Maglin /> in addition to bamboo and recycled plastic knit. Its soles are sourced from sugar-cane based EVA. The insoles are created through a mix of [[Cork (material)|cork]] and [[memory foam]].<ref name=Today /> Styles have included a low top version<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/shop-with-us/news/cariuma-bestselling-oca-low-top-sneakers-back-in-stock/|title=Get the Bestselling Cariuma Low Sneakers Before They Sell Out Again|date=March 6, 2020}}</ref> and an Ibi version.<ref name=Today /> Shoes are shipping to customers in recycled packaging<ref name=Maglin /> and the company purchases carbon offsets to make its shipping carbon neutral.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/02/cnn-underscored/eco-friendly-shoe-brands/index.html|title=Eco-friendly shoes that are as comfortable as they are sustainable|first=Kai|last=Burkhardt|date=March 2, 2020|website=CNN Underscored}}</ref> \nThe company has worked with artists including Elisa Wong, was the official footwear partner of [[Pantone]],<ref name=Parisi /> and is a sponsor of [[Italo Ferreira]] of the [[World Surf League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://footwearnews.com/2020/business/marketing/marketing-fashion-news-campaigns-deals-january-2020-1202896316/|title=Marketing Plays: Bruno Magli Men\u2019s Spring Campaign Focuses on the Modern Renaissance Man+ More News|first1=F. N.|last1=Staff|first2=F. N.|last2=Staff|date=January 22, 2020}}</ref> \n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n[[Category:Shoe companies]]\n[[Category:Shoe brands]]\n[[Category:2016 establishments in Brazil]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Cariuma\n| logo = Cariuma logo.png\n| logo_size = 150px\n| founders = David Python<br>Fernando Porto\n| foundation = 2016\n| industry = Clothing\n| website = {{url|https://cariuma.com/}}\n}}\n'''Cariuma''' is a company that produces and sells shoes.\n\n==History==\nCariuma is a designer and manufacturer of sustainably produced [[Sneakers|sneaker-style shoes]], which it retails through the Internet. It was cofounded in 2016<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://danamic.org/2018/12/29/from-rio-to-singapore-cariuma-sneakers-are-now-exclusively-available-at-kapok-ndc/|title=From Rio To Singapore: CARIUMA Sneakers Are Now Exclusively Available at kapok NDC|date=December 29, 2018|website=DANAMIC}}</ref> by David Python<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/directtoconsumer-sneaker-brand-scores-us13m-seed-funding|title=Tech in Asia - Connecting Asia's startup ecosystem|website=www.techinasia.com}}</ref> and Fernando Porto.<ref name=Today>{{Cite web|url=https://www.today.com/shop/popular-cariuma-ibi-sneakers-are-back-stock-t175607|title=Why over 6,000 people are on the waitlist for these sustainably-made sneakers|website=TODAY.com}}</ref> The manufacturing is based in [[Brazil]]<ref name=Maglin>{{Cite web|url=https://www.travelandleisure.com/style/shopping/cariuma-catiba-low-sneakers|title=These Comfy Sneakers Were Handmade for Walking \u2014 and They\u2019re Completely Sustainable|website=Travel + Leisure}}</ref> and [[China]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fastcompany.com/90418251/these-shoes-are-made-from-bamboo-sugar-cane-and-cork-and-totally-carbon-neutral|title=These shoes are made from bamboo, sugarcane, and cork\u2014and are totally carbon neutral|first=Adele|last=Peters|date=October 21, 2019|website=Fast Company}}</ref> while the has offices in [[Singapore]], [[New York City]], [[Los Angeles]], and [[Rio de Jainero]].<ref name=Parisi>{{Cite web|url=https://www.glossy.co/fashion/1-year-in-how-sneaker-brand-cariuma-is-making-a-1-million-investment-in-sustainability-pay-off|title=1 year in: How sneaker brand Cariuma is making a $1 million investment in sustainability pay off|date=December 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\nCariuma makes its shoes by hand, and uses materials including canvas, leather, and suede,<ref name=Maglin /> in addition to bamboo and recycled plastic knit. Its soles are sourced from sugar-cane based EVA. The insoles are created through a mix of [[Cork (material)|cork]] and [[memory foam]].<ref name=Today /> Styles have included a low top version<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/shop-with-us/news/cariuma-bestselling-oca-low-top-sneakers-back-in-stock/|title=Get the Bestselling Cariuma Low Sneakers Before They Sell Out Again|date=March 6, 2020}}</ref> and an Ibi version.<ref name=Today /> Shoes are shipping to customers in recycled packaging<ref name=Maglin /> and the company purchases carbon offsets to make its shipping carbon neutral.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/02/cnn-underscored/eco-friendly-shoe-brands/index.html|title=Eco-friendly shoes that are as comfortable as they are sustainable|first=Kai|last=Burkhardt|date=March 2, 2020|website=CNN Underscored}}</ref> \nThe company has worked with artists including Elisa Wong, was the official footwear partner of [[Pantone]],<ref name=Parisi /> and is a sponsor of [[Italo Ferreira]] of the [[World Surf League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://footwearnews.com/2020/business/marketing/marketing-fashion-news-campaigns-deals-january-2020-1202896316/|title=Marketing Plays: Bruno Magli Men\u2019s Spring Campaign Focuses on the Modern Renaissance Man+ More News|first1=F. N.|last1=Staff|first2=F. N.|last2=Staff|date=January 22, 2020}}</ref> \n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n[[Category:Shoe companies]]\n[[Category:Shoe brands]]\n[[Category:2016 establishments in Brazil]]\n", "name_user": "Mandarax", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fix typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cariuma"}
